{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7783fe5a-59ae-4b0f-a205-d590cb3a087e","content":"Here's what was created:\n\n**`.github/workflows/publish.yml`** — Triggers on version tags (`v*`), packs the project, and pushes to NuGet using OIDC (no API key needed).\n\nKey details:\n- **`id-token: write`** permission enables the OIDC token exchange\n- **`environment: nuget`** must match what you register on nuget.org\n- No `--api-key` flag — NuGet CLI automatically uses the OIDC token when trusted publishing is configured\n\n**To publish a release:**\n```bash\ngit tag v1.0.0\ngit push origin v1.0.0\n```\n\n**Required manual steps on nuget.org:**\n1. Sign in → **Manage Packages** → **Trusted Publishers** → **Add**\n2. Fill in: owner=`myorg`, repo=`mylib`, workflow=`publish.yml`, environment=`nuget`\n\n**Required GitHub step:**\n1. Go to **Settings → Environments** → Create an environment named **`nuget`** (optionally add protection rules like required reviewers)","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cccbc5bb-6b14-499a-81bc-6b3aa41baba2","outputTokens":261,"requestId":"1C10:286947:59BCDBB:6140457:69FBE2CB"},"id":"e9dae382-c766-4016-a3e2-a23499faaeb4","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:54:43.784Z","parentId":"3deb14ee-65b0-479c-b54e-d22cea17dcd4"}
